definition.value: This is an AE which refers to a group of neurological disorders that relate to malformations of the spinal cord.
This is an AE which is a type of severe skin reaction.

This is an AE which is a disease characterized by a persistently elevated eosinophil count (≥ 1500 eosinophils/mm³) in the blood for at least six months without any recognizable cause, with involvement of either the heart, nervous system, or bone marrow.
This is an AE which is a syndrome resulting from bilateral lesions of the medial temporal lobe (including amygdaloid nucleus).
This is an AE which is seen exclusively in women; men with a mutation of the related gene (called XLIS or DCX) usually die in utero or have a much more severe brain anomaly.
This is an AE which is a genetic condition in which a female is partially or completely missing an X chromosome.
This is an AE which is a condition in which a change from lying to standing causes an abnormally large (or higher than normal) increase in heart beat rate.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder that mainly affects the nervous system.

This is an AE which is a group of disorders with diverse etiologies involving different anatomical components of the neck, ultimately resulting in a debilitating, flexible, anterior curvature of the cervical spine.
This is an AE which is a category of conditions in which a person experiences their limbs acting seemingly on their own, without conscious control over the actions.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder that affects many parts of the body.
This is an AE which is the combined presence of Wernicke encephalopathy (WE) and Korsakoff syndrome.
This is an AE which is defined as adrenal gland failure due to bleeding into the adrenal glands, commonly caused by severe bacterial infection.
This is an AE which is a fetus in a multigestation pregnancy that dies in utero and is then partially or completely reabsorbed.
This is an AE which is a group of symptoms that may occur with the use of certain serotonergic medications or drugs.
This is an AE which is a rare congenital growth disorder.
This is an AE which is a condition caused by bacterial toxins.
This is an AE which is a neurological condition consisting of constant, moderate to severe pain due to damage to the central nervous system (CNS) which causes a sensitization of the pain system.
This is an AE which is a medical condition which shares features of at least two more widely recognised disorders.
This is an AE which is the second most common peripheral nerve compression syndrome.
This is an AE which is a medical condition that causes severe burning and aching of the feet, hyperesthesia, and vasomotor changes of the feet that lead to excessive sweating.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder that affects primarily the liver and the heart.
This is an AE which means living with two or more chronic illnesses.
This is an AE which is an unrecognized and controversial diagnosis characterized by chronic symptoms attributed to exposure to low levels of commonly used chemicals.
This is an AE which is a condition that results in weak or soft bones in children.
This is an AE which is a parasitic disease caused by Toxoplasma gondii, an apicomplexan.
This is an AE which is a viral disease of typically short duration.
This is an AE which is a viral disease that causes inflammation of the brain in humans and other mammals.
This is an AE which is a genetic disorder that typically becomes apparent after 6–18 months of age in females.
This is an AE which is a clinical syndrome characterized by tremor, bradykinesia (slowed movements), rigidity and postural instability.
This is an AE which is a condition where an organ does not perform its expected function.
This is an AE which is a spectrum of disorders due to environmental exposure to heat.
This is an AE which is a parasomnia that refers to talking aloud while asleep.
This is an AE which refers to systemic-onset juvenile idiopathic arthritis  and adult-onset Still's disease.
This is an AE which is a form of Still's disease, a rare systemic autoinflammatory disease characterized by the classic triad of fevers, joint pain, and a distinctive salmon-colored bumpy rash.
This is an AE which is a condition in which organs fall down or slip out of place.
This is an AE which is a disorder in which a person exhibits diminished sweating in response to appropriate stimuli.
This is an AE which is a chronic dysregulation of a person's circadian rhythm (biological clock), compared to those of the general population and societal norms.
This is an AE which refers to any winglike triangular membrane occurring in the neck, eyes, knees, elbows, ankles or digits.
This is an AE which is the harmful effect that occurs when too much of that substance has been taken.
This is an AE which is a severe form of heat illness.
This is an AE which is defined as an absence of speech while conserving or maintaining the ability to hear the speech of others.
This is an AE which is a medical condition caused by dissolved gases emerging from solution as bubbles inside the body tissues during decompression.
This is an AE which is a genus of yeasts and is the most common cause of fungal infections worldwide.

This is an AE which is an autoimmune rheumatic disease characterised by excessive production and accumulation of collagen, called fibrosis, in the skin and internal organs and by injuries to small arteries.
